Colombia's largest and most reliable news source.

18.description:
Since being founded in 2008, Colombia Reports has unrelentingly striven to deliver news about Colombia to people around the world as accurately as possible. This is reinforced by the fact that they are independent and are not affiliated with any political or social organization.

Colombia Reports is Colombia’s main news source published exclusively in English and has received international recognition. They are frequently cited by major media outlets such as the New York Times, BBC, CNN, The Huffington Post and Fox News.

Headquartered in Medellin, Colombia Reports is often referred to as ‘The Free Voice of Colombia’. Their objective is to accurately correspond what happens in Colombia to a global audience.

Their fast-growing team is made up of professional journalists, photographers, and expatriates from the Americas, Europe and Australia. Besides this, they train local aspiring journalists to think critically and independently and hope to enrich Colombia with a new generation of conscientious, high caliber journalists.
